reviews.text: Lovely guest house. Hong Kong style room (ie. small) but clean and comfortable. Had an excellent sleep there after leaving a terrible hostel. Perfect for a couple on a budget.

Small but has everything you need for a basic, comfortable stay. Location is very strategic with restaurants, shopping, train station, ferry terminals all within walking distance. The owners are also very helpful and friendly.
Samuel and his wife were great even lending us an umbrella when it started raining

Friendly owner, room make up everyday, clean room also very clean and up to date bathroom, spacious bathroom compare to other hostel, and most importantly at the heart of tsim sha tsui... Awesome...
Very recommended, definitely will go back if travelling to HK again.
Great location very central easy access to train (MRT) rooms exceptionaly clean (small but functional) both Samuel and Fannie are great hosts and extremely helpful. Plenty of food houses around.
